				<div class="job_detail">
					<h1 class="positiontitle">Autodesk欧特克软件公司招聘实习生</h1>
					<div class="spacer"></div>
					<div class="spacer4"></div>
						<p>
该职位已发布超过<span class="pdlr or">423</span>天

						<span class="pdlr"></span><span>编号：200846</span>
						<span class="pdlr"></span></p>
					<div class="spacer"></div>
					<p>						
						<span>工作地区：上海</span>
						<span class="pdlr"></span>
						<span>更新时间：2012-05-30</span>
					</p>
<div style="border-top:1px solid #C3DBE8; margin-top: 8px;"></div>
					<div class="spacer"></div>
					<div class="spacer"></div>
					<div style="overflow:auto;">
						<p>【Autodesk R &amp; D招聘 &ndash; Intern Positions】<br />
As a global leader in 3D design, engineering, and entertainment software, Autodesk helps people imagine, design, and create a better world. Autodesk accelerates better design through an unparalleled depth of experience and a broad portfolio of software to give customers the power to solve their design, business, and environmental challenges. In addition to designers, architects, engineers, and media and entertainment professionals, Autodesk helps students, educators, and casual creators unlock their creative ideas through user-friendly applications.</p>
<p>Working Location: Autodesk China Research &amp; Development &ndash; Shanghai<br />
Internship Requirement: At least 3-day attendance to the work is required, and the internship is required to last for 6-12 months</p>
<p>Resumes send to: gracie.zheng@autodesk.com</p>
<p><br />
Position 1: Intern &ndash; Software Engineer</p>
<p>Responsibilities:<br />
-	Design, prototype, implement, test and troubleshoot product features and components according to the market requirements and product specifications.<br />
-	Design, implement, test and maintain engineering tools to make the whole team more efficient<br />
-	Deliver results that meet market requirements and product specifications with a high level of quality and customer satisfaction.<br />
-	Work closely with Test Development group in unit level testing and problem resolution.</p>
<p>Requirements:<br />
-	Majored in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Math, GIS or relevant<br />
-	In school student who will graduate in 2012 or 2013, Master degree candidate preferred<br />
-	3 days/week available for on-site working<br />
-	Hands-on experience with native C and .Net programming<br />
-	In-depth knowledge of algorithms and design patterns<br />
-	Fluent oral English</p>
<p>Preferred Qualifications:<br />
-	Experience on mobile development or cloud computing is a plus</p>
<p><br />
Position 2: Intern &ndash; Software Developer (Web)</p>
<p>Responsibilities:<br />
-	Working as a C# Developer in a cross-functional Agile development team. <br />
-	Developing web product software leverage object-oriented design, development, and code reuse. <br />
-	Design, implement, test and troubleshoot. <br />
-	Work as a member of an integrated team collaborating closely with team members in US. <br />
-	Estimate time requirements for assigned projects. Deliver assignments on time, adhering to pre-determined specification and quality standards.</p>
<p>Requirements: <br />
-	BS or MS degree in Computer Science or related technical discipline (or equivalent)<br />
-	Strong programming capabilities on web application development on .Net C#.<br />
-	Experience on .Net Framework 3.5/4.0 development; understand Linq, WCF, NHibernate would be a plus. <br />
-	Familiar with DIV CSS, Javascript; knowledge on MSSQL or MYSQL or Oracle. <br />
-	Familiar with internet applications, understanding on the trend of internet development.<br />
-	Excellent analytical, design and troubleshooting skills. <br />
-	Highly motivated and self-directed individual. <br />
-	Good written and verbal communication skills in the English language (Pass CET Band 4).</p>
<p>Desired Knowledge/Skills: <br />
-	Real industry product development experience <br />
-	Familiar with Agile development process</p>
<p>Position 3: Intern - Software Developer (Mobile)</p>
<p>Responsibilities:<br />
-	As part of the intern program, you need to work closely with your mentor and team to learn required knowledge, participate in the real project implementation and grow your expertise and experience in real project fields.<br />
-	Design and implement of features in mobile products<br />
-	Implement image process algorithm to enhance the drawing applications capability on mobile<br />
-	Research and prototype with new image processing technology to support new drawing and image process software<br />
-	Participate in technical design and code review to ensure that our design and code meets high standards</p>
<p>Requirements:<br />
-	Good knowledge of image processing <br />
-	Experience with development on drawing or image processing software<br />
-	Strong C background<br />
-	Optional Desired Attributes:<br />
o	Project experience with mobile platforms like iOS or Andriod</p>
<p>Education:<br />
-	Candidates of BS or MS in Computer Science or related field.</p>
<p>Position 4: Intern - Software Developer (Graphics)</p>
<p>General Summary:<br />
Autodesk Inc., a world leader in 2D and 3D design, engineering, and entertainment software, helps people imagine, design, and create a better world. Autodesks advanced visual effects and finishing systems are used by thousands of artists to produce television commercials and shows, music videos, and blockbuster movies. The Creative Finishing team is currently seeking highly motivated individuals that are looking for the challenges and rewards of working in a collaborative and energized environment, and in developing state of the art processing pipeline and rendering technologies.</p>
<p>Requirements:<br />
-	Major in Computer Science or related degree.<br />
-	Excellent C programming skills with related technologies like STL and boost.<br />
-	Good knowledge of OO design and programming techniques.<br />
-	Good understanding of computer architecture.<br />
-	Experience with 3D and rendering techniques needed. <br />
-	Experience with OpenGL, GLSL, CG, or DirectX. <br />
-	Experience in GPU shader development and performance optimization beneficial.<br />
-	Understanding of compositing and image processing techniques beneficial. <br />
-	Familiarity developing on Linux and Mac OS. <br />
-	Familiarity with Python preferred.<br />
-	Excellent oral and written communication skills.</p>
<p><br />
Position 5: Intern &ndash; SQA</p>
<p>The position is for part-time Quality Assurance engineer with a passion and commitment to developing quality software through quality assurance best practices. The candidate should have certain understanding of software QA methodologies and process.</p>
<p>Principal Duties and Responsibilities:<br />
-	Design, implement, execute and maintain black box, grey box and API test strategies for new and existing Autodesk ICP Group products.<br />
-	Develop, execute and maintain software test designs and test suites will include both GUI and API level tests(C#, .Net, PHP and etc.)<br />
-	Report defects/issues and verify code fixes during the release cycle.<br />
-	Develop and implement automation tests to increase effective regression coverage.<br />
-	Participates in estimating and planning software testing tasks for themselves.<br />
-	Logs defects in database for tracking and reporting.</p>
<p>Requirements:<br />
-	The 1st or 2nd year student of Master Degree or 3rd year student of Bachelor degree in Computer Science or related.<br />
-	On-site work at least 4 working days a week.<br />
-	Solid background in Software Engineering or/and Quality Assurance techniques, process, practices and methodologies.<br />
-	Solid understanding of C# or .NET or Java or PHP programming<br />
-	Familiar with SQL Server, Oracle, and other RDBMS.<br />
-	Hands-on experience with troubleshooting technical problems.<br />
-	Strong written and oral communication skills.</p>
<p>Position 6: Intern &ndash; QA Analyst (Maya)</p>
<p>Be a part of the Autodesk Maya team - working in the forefront of computer graphics in the entertainment industry. This is a great opportunity for a student in campus to join the Maya product development team in Shanghai and act the roll as a user analyst QA.</p>
<p>Responsibilities:<br />
-	Creates plans to test features or whole products at the user interface level, including workflow tests, production style tests, and interoperability tests.<br />
-	Executes tests to find defects in features or products. Isolates and confirms defects and works with developers to prioritize defects and fix them.<br />
-	Validates the behaviour of software on a variety of operating systems and hardware.<br />
-	Logs defects in database for tracking and reporting, and provides accurate evaluation of software quality and reliability to the team leader.<br />
-	Participates in team meetings throughout the product development life cycle. Works with the development team to proactively recognize and prevent issues from occurring.<br />
-	Reviews and tests product documentation. <br />
-	Estimates, plans, schedules and coordinates software testing tasks for themselves and co-ordinates with others.<br />
-	Participates in release to manufacturing, release to web, Alpha and Beta release activities.</p>
<p>Requirements:<br />
-	BS or higher in Digit Media Arts relevant<br />
-	Good at Autodesk Maya <br />
-	Clear verbal and written English communication skills<br />
-	Works well in a team environment<br />
-	Keen eye for detail, meticulous and analytically minded<br />
-	Adaptable and flexible</p>
<p>Additional Knowledge or Skills <br />
-	Knowledge of Windows, Linux and Mac OS X<br />
-	Good understand for other Autodesk 3D animation applications</p>
<p><br />
Position 7: Intern &ndash; Product Designer (工业设计专业)</p>
<p>Responsibilities:<br />
-	As part of the intern program, you need to work closely with your mentor and team to learn required knowledge, participate in the real project implementation and grow your expertise and experience in real project fields.<br />
-	In this role, you will work with our designers to create a better user experience, and help develop a genuine look and feel for our products. As part of the intern program, you will work closely with your mentor and team to learn required knowledge, participate in the real project implementation, and grow your expertise in real project fields. You will work closely with our designers, and have opportunity meeting with our customers to validate existing and future feature design.</p>
<p>Requirements:<br />
-	Passion for creating enchanting user experiences, and a commitment to excellence <br />
-	A portfolio demonstrating superior visual or interactive design <br />
-	Demonstrate interest in the details and the results of the design process, not just the initial high concept<br />
-	Ability to develop interactive prototypes to aid evaluation and development of designs using Axure RP, Flash Catalyst, or equivalence is a big plus.<br />
-	Additional desired knowledge (an asset for the role)<br />
o	Desktop, Web or mobile design experience/knowledge.<br />
o	Good aesthetic judgment<br />
o	Verbal and written fluency in the English language</p>
<p>Education:<br />
-	BS or MS in human-computer interaction, industrial design, interior design, multimedia design, or a related field</p>
<p>Position 8: Intern &ndash; Digital Arts (工业设计、美术专业)</p>
<p>Responsibilities:<br />
-	As part of the intern program, you need to work closely with your mentor and team to learn required knowledge, participate in the real project implementation and grow your expertise and experience in real project fields.<br />
-	Provide industry insights and domain knowledge throughout the software development lifecycle, influence product planning and design by actively participating in product plan review and concept design review and discussion.<br />
-	Write test plan and test case for assigned project of feature. <br />
-	Execute feature testing according to feature spec, and track defects along the entire development cycle.<br />
-	Develop and execute comprehensive workflow test plans assuring the overall quality of the product.<br />
Requirements:<br />
-	Love and passion in sketch is a must have for this position.<br />
-	Excellent problem solving skills: You have a &ldquo;never give up&rdquo; attitude.<br />
-	Be passionate in testing and never compromise in quality.<br />
-	Excellent written or oral communication skill in English.<br />
-	Good team work.<br />
-	Good customer orientation and interpersonal skills and responsiveness.</p>
<p>Education:<br />
-	Candidates of BS or MS in Industry Design or related field.</p>
<p><br />
关于Autodesk中国研究院<br />
成立于2008年1月的Autodesk中国研究院（简称ACRD）是建立在原有的Autodesk中国应用开发中心（简称CADC）、及新并购的汉略信息技术有限公司（简称HSL）基础上的，是Autodesk公司全球最大的研发基地。该中心集中了国内外一大批专业技术精英，全面参与公司各大主营产品的核心研发工作。产品所涉及的领域涵盖机械设计、空间地理信息系统、三维数字娱乐、动画设计及软件开发、基础设施工程、建筑设计、数据交换等，用户遍布全球各地。100％《财富》100强公司及98％《财富》500强公司均为Autodesk的客户。<br />
关于Autodesk<br />
Autodesk欧特克软件公司，作为世界领先的二维、三维数字化设计及管理软件，以及数字化内容供应商，不断向制造业、工程建设行业、地理信息业以及传媒娱乐业提供卓越的数字化软件服务和解决方案。自1982年AutoCAD正式推向市场，欧特克软件公司已针对最广泛的应用领域研发出多种先进的数字样机解决方案，帮助用户在设计转化为成品前体验自己的创意。在数字设计市场，没有哪家公司能在产品的品种和市场占有率方面与Autodesk匹敌。作为世界上最大的软件公司之一，欧特克软件公司的用户遍及150多个国家，数量超过七百万。<br />
Autodesk欧特克软件公司以为员工提供具有吸引力的薪酬制度、良好的福利待遇及令人称道的工作环境所著称。了解更多关于欧特克软件公司信息，请查询：www.autodesk.com &amp; www.autodesk.com.cn &nbsp;</p>					</div>
